e explanation re: the pause in warming of the climate for past 16 years (and continuing!)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In a scat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">hing article, Ms Judith Curry (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a respected atmospheric scientist at the Georgia Institute of Technology Atlanta USA) wrote: “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Kill the IPCC!</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> After years</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> and billions (of dollars), IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> has failed to document</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">a link</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">between </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">human-CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> emission and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> warming of the earth’s climate!”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As this bitter debate continues unabated, it is important to closely look at the reality of climate change as revealed by observ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ations. Among some of t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">realities of climate change</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> are:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The earth’s climate has warmed by about 0.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6C to 0.8C in the last 50 years</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Most of this warming appears to have occurred from about </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1978</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> till 1998 or so. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The earth’s climate has NOT warmed further</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> since abo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ut mid-1998 till now. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Worldwide human-CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> emissions have increa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sed continuously over the last 60 years or so. Since the World War II, worldwide industrial activity has added about 275 billion tons of CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in the earth’s atmosphere. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tmospheric </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">concentration of CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> has risen from a value of about 356ppmv</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">parts per million, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">volume</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> basis</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">) in 1956 to about 400ppmv at present</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. Atmospheric CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is just </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">about </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">0.04% of the ‘total air that we breathe!’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Climate of the Twentieth Century:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Before we consid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">er several other issues on the present climate change debate, it is important to look at the earth’s climate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and growth of atmospheric CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for the twentieth century, for which best observational information is now available.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The earth’s climate warmed ste</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eply by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">about 0.5C from 19</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">10 till 1945</span><span style="color:#ff6600; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The human-CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> emissions were minimal then!</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The earth’s climate cooled by about 0.25C between</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 1945-1977 period, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in spite of  rapid increase of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> human-CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> emissions (soon after World War II). </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The earth’s climate warmed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by about 0.6C since 1977.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Since mid 1998 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the earth’s climate has stopped warming further.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Human-CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> emissions have continued to rise </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and in fact have escalated  in recent years</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">When careful</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ly analyzed, these observational lampposts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> suggest that “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">the lin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">k between human-CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> emissions and climate warming remains</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> questionable as ever!”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Issues Re:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> IPCC AR5 SPM-Summary for Policymakers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">How robust ar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e IPCC AR5 Conclusions? The IPCC AR5 reiterates what it has said in its earlier</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (2007)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">climate change documents. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> IPCC AR5 has once again portrayed a narrow focus about climate and climate change be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing driven primarily by human-CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> emissions. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.67pt; padding-left:3.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IPCC AR5 has failed to address criticism of previous reports. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It has underestimated the role of sun</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and/or natural variability (via changes in large-scale atmosphere-ocean </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">circulation </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">patterns) on climate and climate change. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Can any areas of climate change science be considered as settled now? NO! IPCC ha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s not thoroughly examined the linkage between at</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mospheric CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and eart</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">h’s climate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in the historical and geological past. </span><span style="color:#ff6600; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="color:#ff6600; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IPCC AR5 SPM does NOT adequately explain uncertainty in many of its claim</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> about present climate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">change </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">OR projections of future warming of the climate. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IPCC AR5 makes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> NO attempt </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to address reliability of climate models. None of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="color:#ff6600; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">climate models have been verified against observations. It is easy to do this, by running a suite o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f models in shorter timeframe (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">say two to five years) and then verify the forecast parameters like m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">an temperature, precipitation etc against observed values. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Further, IPCC AR5 makes NO attempt to explain why climate models have over-predicted warming by more than</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 200% than the observed warming since the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">new </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">millennium!</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30pt; padding-left:6pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There is NO explanation about the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> hiatus in the warming of the climate for the past 16 years! Further, the IPCC AR5 has totally ignored the reality of climate change in the past few years! The reality being that Cold Weather Extremes have increased </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">worldwide! For example: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Most of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Europ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">witnessed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">significantly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">colder winters</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> since the new millennium, with several hundred people dying of extreme cold in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Eastern</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Europe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in particular. (recent cold winters in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Europe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 2005/06, 2009/10, 2011/12 and 2012/13</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">).</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Most of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">South America</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> wit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nessed colder winte</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2007, 2010</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and most recently in July 2013, with several dozen deaths in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Argentina</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Chile</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3).</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Northern India</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> has witnessed much colder winters since last five years, resulting in several hundred deaths. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Dangerous Climate Change</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: There is NO dangerous warming of the earth’s climate anyw</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">here! The climate has warmed only modestly so far! This modest warming has been beneficial to world humanity, esp. for South Asian nations, where increased grain and food yields</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (due to more CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> ac</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ting</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> as a fer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tilizer)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> have improved socio-economic status of some 2.5 billion people in last 30 years!</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Human health has also improved significantly in most nations in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">South Asia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.67pt; padding-left:3.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Reducing (Or Cutting) CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times 