ons o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f human-CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> provides NO substantive evidence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to support this claim</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">!</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Further the SPM </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">fail</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d to explain the hiatus in the warming for the last 16 years! </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Finally the SPM has totally ignored the reality of earth’s climate, which is that “The earth’s climate now appe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ars to be entering into a colder epoch!</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> With the approaching of the solar grand minima in the next decade or about, there is now a distinct possibility that the earth’s climate could see an onset of an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Ice Age </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">type climate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in the next two to three decades</spa